description: The basketball court at Jack Stephens Center was so badly damaged from freezing temperatures that the school is unsure if it will be playable again this season.

title: Los Angeles police confirm Rapper Theophilus London reported missing by family
description: Theophilus London, a rapper who has collaborated with artist like Kanye West and Travis Scott, has been reported missing by his family in Los Angeles on Wednesday.

title: New York police officers stabbed, suspect shot and killed
description: Two New York police officers were stabbed Wednesday and the suspect was fatally shot, authorities said.

title: Cardinals 'had no idea' JJ Watt was retiring, head coach says
description: J.J. Watt is having his best season in the last few years, which explains why head coach Kliff Kingsbury had "no idea" he was retiring at the end of the season.

title: Southwest Airlines flight diverted to Milwaukee due to 'potential mechanical issue' amid cancellation chaos
description: Southwest Airlines had to divert a flight to Milwaukee on Wednesday due to a "potential mechanical issue" as the airline recovers after thousands of flights were canceled.

title: Gunman, 9 others convicted in near-fatal shooting of Red Sox legend David Ortiz
description: A Dominican Republic court convicted 10 of the 13 defendants accused of attempting to murder Hall of Famer David “Big Papi” Ortiz in Santo Domingo in June 2019.

title: Elaine Chao warns of more scrutiny following airlines' 'total nightmare' over Christmas
description: Former Transportation Secretary Elaine L. Chao reacted to the chaos at American airports after Southwest and other airlines canceled flights over the holiday

title: MSNBC host Menendez and Rep. Castro slam GOP for 'Christian' hypocrisy on immigration policy
description: MSNBC host Alicia Menendez, filling in for Alex Wagner, slammed Republican leaders and the party itself from a religious hypocrisy angle, for not being hospitable enough to migrants.
